cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a new SVM model for joint learning of feature transformation and classifier, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The proposed model is applied to both UCI machine learning datasets and LFW face datasets, indicating a focus on computer vision and image processing, which falls under "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of kernel principal component analysis, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and falls under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The use of gradient descent and existing SVM solver suggests a focus on neural networks and optimization, which falls under "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the minimization of radius and margin, which is a topic in optimization and falls under "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
